"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386565","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-07-07","<p>The Government is committed to building 200,000 Starter Homes over the course of this Parliament, to be offered exclusively for young first time buyers at 20% below their market value. The Housing Bill will take forward legislation to ensure the delivery of Starter Homes.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2015-07-07T14:44:03.067Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386565/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386565/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386565/answer",,,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-06-30","Housing: Construction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what progress he has made on rolling out the Starter Homes initiative; and how many homes he expects to be available under that scheme by the end of the year.","false","Biography information for Tulip Siddiq","Hampstead and Kilburn","Tulip Siddiq","4885"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386566","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-07-14","<p>Under the Code of Practice for Ministerial Appointments to Public Bodies April 2012, Government Departments are required to publicise successful appointments.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-07-14T08:50:27.683Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386566/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386566/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386566/answer",,,,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-06-30","Department for Culture, Media and Sport: Public Appointments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, if he will place in the Library a list of all public appointments made by his Department between 1 January 2015 and 1 May 2015.","false","Biography information for Dame Margaret Hodge","Barking","Margaret Hodge","4961"
